NOTE="css-values layout subset exposed via the modulePrefixes [\"calc-\"] entry in wpt.json (the rest of the suite is testharness computed-value / serialization tests the layout-tree compare runner cannot grade, filtered out by isScriptHarnessTest). 34 of 46 layout-gradeable calc() fixtures pass, including the calc()-through-sizing cases unblocked by mizchi/css 0.4.2 mixed calc() (issue #67: calc-{max,min}-width-block-* / calc-width-block-1), the fixed-table overflow growth from issue #281 (calc-width-table-fixed-1's first table), and abspos percentage-height-vs-ICB (calc-in-calc / calc-parenthesis-stack, fixed in #282). The 12 known failures are separate residuals: fixed/auto table remaining-width column distribution (calc-width-table-fixed-1 / -auto-1 -- Chromium distributes leftover width to mixed-calc vs pure-% columns idiosyncratically), calc() containing an intrinsic keyword resolving to 0 (calc-width-block-intrinsic-1), max()/min() math functions (calc-in-max), min-width/min-height block height (calc-min-width-block-1 / calc-min-height), calc rounding (calc-rounding-001 / -003), ch/ex font units (calc-ch-ex-lang), gradient (calc-background-image-gradient-1), transform-origin (calc-transform-origin-1), and vertical-align (calc-vertical-align-1). Pins 34/46 as a no-regression gate; widening the prefix and closing the residuals is follow-up work (tracked in #282). Measured with the vendored Tinos text metric (tests/wpt-fonts)."
